Incident.Summary: Check Theft/Fraud /Florence Faye Wastler / Wastler and Son Inc // 2640 Sumantown Road, Middletown, Frederick

IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeText: This incident was audio and video recorded on a body-worn camera. ATTACHMENTS: - Copy of the check - Affidavit of Unauthorized Action - Witness Statement VICTIM/COMPLAINANT: -Florence Faye Wastler (08/30/1967) Suspect - Christopher Kendrick NEIGHBORHOOD CHECK - N/A SCENE PROCESSING: N/A Narrative On Wednesday, July 12, 2023, I responded to 2640 Sumantown Rd, Frederick, Frederick County, Maryland, for a report of a check fraud/theft. Upon Arrival, I made contact with the complainant Florence Faye Wastler (08/30/1967.) Wastler advised that on 07/12/2023 at approximately 1038 hours, she received a phone call from Middletown Valley Bank advising her of a suspicious check related to her account. The bank advised that a check bearing her signature and business name (Wastler Son, Inc.), which was made payable to LB Water Services had been altered to a different name (Christopher Kendrick). I observed a copy of the check bearing an amount of 22,149.55 dollars. However, the legal line on the check reflected a different amount of twenty-thousand one hundred and forty-nine dollars and fifty-five cents. The bank advised that they had completed a payment amount of $22,149.55 to Christopher Kendrick. I conducted a follow-up at the Middletown Valley Bank located at 3848 Jefferson Pike, Jefferson, Frederick County, Maryland, and made contact with Meredith Reeves (Retail Branch Manager). Reeves contacted the Middletown Valley Bank back office and advised that the bank was going to return the stolen amount back to the victims account (Wastler and Son, Inc). I subsequently called Wastler and advised her accordingly of the new development. I further informed her that I was going to proceed with investigating the crime and identifying the suspect. All events occurred in Frederick County, Maryland. Case Status: Open, pending investigation.
